Combine rhubarb and sugar in a large saucepan. Stir in 1 cup water. Cook and stir on medium heat until mixture comes to a boil, then continue to boil for 2 min. Remove from heat. Stir in gelatin until completely dissolved. Pour evenly into 7 dessert cups. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Garnish each serving with 1 Tbsp. thawed COOL WHIP Whipped Topping and a strawberry, if desired.